cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a language-conditional generative model for interpreting natural language messages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a listening agent's policy to condition on the visual grounding of the message. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper introduces a generative model and discusses losses framed specifically for their model-based formulation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper discusses visual grounding and incorporating observations outside of the listening agent's field-of-view. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the paper discusses speaker-listener navigation tasks.
